@node Der Level-Inspektor, , Einstellungen, Ganz zu Anfang
@subsection Der Level-Inspektor

To view more detail information about a level you can call the level inspector.
Just right or control click on the level's preview image in the level menu.

You can compare your scores to the world record, the par, the level author's
score. Even some statistics about how many players solved a level are provided.

Besides all the other information that is described in detail in the reference
manual you can enter a small annotation to a level and can rate the level.

Please note the annotation text field may allow you just to enter ASCII 
characters depending on the system Enigma is running.

The rating is your personal impression of the level. @samp{-} stands for no
opinion. 0 - for very bad, 5 - for average, 10 - for best of best. The ratings
will be sent back with your scores (@pxref{Ergebnisse hochladen}).

Last but not least you can use the Level Inspector to view screen shots that 
you made while playing a level (@pxref{Steuerung}).


